    h2.ls3 Colours

    p.f3
        | Eezo comes with the ability to change colours of some
        | properties such as <strong>text</strong>, <strong>background-color</strong>
        | and <strong>borders</strong>. The colours can also be customised in sass
        | by changing the default values or adding more colours.


    h3.ls2.mar-t100 Default Colours

    p
        | These are the default colours that come with eezo, they are
        | mostly just nice defaults for general UI purposes
        | with a slightly cool hue for greys.

    p
        | The <code>black</code> and <code>white</code> colors are bot set 
        | to "nicer" shade with zero saturation. Where as the greys are 
        | slightly saturated with a cool hue. (<a href="http://ianstormtaylor.com/design-tip-never-use-black/">
        | why? read this.</a>)

